VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(std::printf|std::fprintf)\s*\(
WHEN EXPR MISSING:"%s"|"%d"|"%f"|"%i"|"%u"|"%x" && MISSING:const\s+char\s*\*\s*format
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects unsafe use of format strings with `printf`-like functions.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Format String Misuse in C++ Streams.
